Durban - Seven informal homes have gone up in flames in Canelands, north of Durban, on Tuesday afternoon. Prem Balram, Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) said Rusa responded to the scene on the incident after receiving numerous calls from residents in the area asking for help. “Upon arrival Reaction Officers found that some of the homes were completely destroyed,” said Balram. He said seven families were left homeless as seven homes were left destroyed but residents had managed to salvage some household items. “The eThekwini Fire Department were called to the scene and doused the fire that had spread to several homes. There were no reported injuries,” he said.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
